WEBVTT

00:05.916 --> 00:07.750
Man: Jake!

00:10.787 --> 00:12.621
[thunder]

00:15.992 --> 00:18.360
Take it easy.
Take it easy.

00:18.428 --> 00:19.895
Uhh! Stop!

00:19.962 --> 00:21.597
Get his limbs.

00:23.000 --> 00:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:44.453 --> 00:45.720
Epileptic?

00:45.788 --> 00:47.054
Not that I know of.

00:47.122 --> 00:48.723
Let's go.

00:58.766 --> 01:01.968
[siren]

01:16.884 --> 01:18.617
So what was it?

01:18.685 --> 01:21.354
Severe allergic reaction.

01:22.923 --> 01:24.257
Oh, he did it on purpose.

01:24.325 --> 01:26.092
He's suicidal?

01:26.160 --> 01:28.127
He's homicidal.

01:28.195 --> 01:30.196
I've found there
ain't much difference.

01:30.264 --> 01:32.764
You know, I never have figured out
why they call you in.

01:32.832 --> 01:35.968
What's the point of saving
a scumbag like this?

01:36.035 --> 01:38.670
He'll only kill someone else
the second he gets a chance.

01:38.738 --> 01:40.138
That's above my pay grade.

01:40.206 --> 01:43.508
Overcrowded anyway.

01:43.576 --> 01:47.111
You think the taxpayers
want to save this idiot?

02:59.447 --> 03:02.149
[groaning]

03:04.618 --> 03:07.519
[gasps]

03:10.723 --> 03:12.959
Put it down.

03:17.897 --> 03:19.898
Don't you go doing
nothing stupid, boy.

03:19.967 --> 03:23.268
'Cause I'll tell you why.

03:23.336 --> 03:26.938
They'll never let you
out of that damn hole again.

03:27.873 --> 03:32.310
Put...it...down.

03:37.850 --> 03:39.216
That's it.

03:52.563 --> 03:54.365
Yeah.

03:54.432 --> 03:56.132
[grunts]

04:01.205 --> 04:03.506
That's it, boy.

04:04.741 --> 04:06.109
That's it.

04:06.176 --> 04:08.544
Uhh! Uhh...

04:11.314 --> 04:12.747
[groans]

04:16.552 --> 04:18.853
[whimpering]

04:18.921 --> 04:24.092
[choking]

04:26.062 --> 04:29.330
Ok, you never give your vote on
who should get what.

04:29.398 --> 04:30.797
Give Reid the mug.

04:30.865 --> 04:32.966
Really? That means that JJ gets
the double-decker bus?

04:33.035 --> 04:34.468
I thought that
was for Kevin.

04:34.536 --> 04:35.836
No, we're not talking
right now.

04:35.904 --> 04:38.472
Garcia, you guys
were just talking yest--

04:38.540 --> 04:40.007
never mind.

04:40.075 --> 04:42.076
Wait, where is everybody?

04:42.144 --> 04:44.710
Don't tell me
they're still in Seattle.

04:44.778 --> 04:47.347
Hi! Hey!
You guys are back. Hi.

04:47.415 --> 04:49.049
Oh, my made it.
Give me a squeeze.

04:49.116 --> 04:50.383
Oh, you guys look great.

04:50.451 --> 04:51.884
[English accent] Cheers.
How's it going?

04:51.952 --> 04:52.952
How's Emily doing?

04:53.020 --> 04:54.587
Brilliant and lovely.

04:54.655 --> 04:56.189
Her apartment's
off the chain.

04:56.257 --> 04:57.490
You mean her flat.

04:57.558 --> 04:59.058
You have to take a shaky old lift
to get to the top,

04:59.125 --> 05:00.725
but the view
is brilliant.

05:00.793 --> 05:02.061
For my favorite bloke.

05:02.128 --> 05:03.695
Hey, I love it!
Thank you!

05:03.729 --> 05:04.663
Thanks.
How was temporary duty?

05:04.730 --> 05:06.165
Oh, it was around the clock.

05:06.232 --> 05:08.467
I thought I'd get a little
more of a vacation, but...

05:08.535 --> 05:09.801
Did you watch
the Olympics at all?

05:09.869 --> 05:10.869
I did see a little
track and field,

05:10.937 --> 05:12.504
but the queen bee here,
she saw everything.

05:12.572 --> 05:15.173
Emily is for real hooked up
over there.

05:15.240 --> 05:17.141
She sends her love. And tea
of the month starts next week.

05:17.209 --> 05:18.409
Ohh. I miss her.

05:18.477 --> 05:20.078
Don't even get me started.

05:20.145 --> 05:22.012
Hey, how's the new?
Is she nice?

05:22.081 --> 05:22.947
Yeah, she is.

05:23.014 --> 05:24.515
I'm just asking.
Reid, do you know

05:24.583 --> 05:25.950
when she was recruited
she was 24?

05:26.017 --> 05:28.419
I've guest lectured in her
forensic linguistics class before.

05:28.487 --> 05:30.321
Of course you have, 'cause she's
a professor and an agent,

05:30.389 --> 05:31.421
which is so impressive.

05:31.489 --> 05:33.190
Mm-hmm.
No, really, she's great.

05:33.257 --> 05:34.357
And driven, clearly.

05:34.425 --> 05:36.493
Berkeley grad,
double major, Bureau star

05:36.561 --> 05:38.195
of the Unabomber case.
And she teaches at Georgetown.

05:38.229 --> 05:40.730
When she's not doing that, she's
SSAing at the Washington Field Office,

05:40.798 --> 05:41.848
and she's a Ph.D.

05:41.873 --> 05:43.567
Does that mean I have
to call her doctor? What?!

05:43.568 --> 05:45.868
I did some research on her
'cause I couldn't sleep on the plane.

05:45.936 --> 05:48.723
And my point is, clearly,
she is smart and capable,

05:48.748 --> 05:50.372
but is she nice?

05:50.373 --> 05:51.740
[Clears throat]

05:52.942 --> 05:54.210
Oh, dear God,
this is happening,

05:54.244 --> 05:56.678
where I talk
and the person is behind...

05:56.746 --> 05:58.714
Me.

05:58.781 --> 06:00.082
The origin of "nice"

06:00.150 --> 06:01.984
is 12th century
middle English,

06:02.051 --> 06:03.684
meaning foolish
or stupid.

06:03.752 --> 06:06.154
I hope you're referring
to the modern use of the adjective.

06:08.257 --> 06:09.957
You must be Penelope.

06:10.025 --> 06:11.859
I'm Alex Blake.

06:11.927 --> 06:13.392
Nice to meet you.

06:13.417 --> 06:15.417
Really, actually nice
in the nicest of ways nice.

06:15.964 --> 06:18.433
I'm Derek Morgan.

06:18.501 --> 06:19.633
Welcome back.

06:19.700 --> 06:21.135
How was Seattle?

06:21.202 --> 06:23.803
The unsub made Ridgeway
look like a saint.

06:23.871 --> 06:26.306
He even used his own kid
to bait the victims.

06:26.374 --> 06:29.375
Well, we've seen that before.
No doubt we'll see it again.

06:29.443 --> 06:30.643
Don't unpack.

06:30.710 --> 06:31.744
Garcia, the files.

06:31.811 --> 06:34.480
Yeah. The files. Oh, God.

06:35.616 --> 06:37.150
A few hours ago
there was a prison transfer

06:37.217 --> 06:39.152
to the county hospital
in Abilene, Texas.

06:39.219 --> 06:41.354
The ambulance crashed
and the prisoner escaped.

06:41.421 --> 06:43.388
He's wearing
the EMT uniform,

06:43.456 --> 06:45.723
and he's armed
with the guard's weapon.

06:45.791 --> 06:47.425
Aren't the U.S. Marshals
on this?

06:47.493 --> 06:49.827
Yes, they are,
but they need your help

06:49.895 --> 06:54.166
because this is what
they found inside.

06:54.233 --> 06:57.569
The EMT and the driver
died in the accident.

06:57.637 --> 06:59.570
The guard, however,
suffocated.

07:00.405 --> 07:03.240
Blake:
What's on his mouth?

07:03.308 --> 07:05.342
It was sewn shut.

07:05.410 --> 07:08.111
So the prisoner
is the Silencer.

07:08.146 --> 07:09.680
Or this guy's a copycat.

07:09.747 --> 07:12.449
Forensics confirmed it's the
same unique double-knot ligature

07:12.517 --> 07:13.817
he used
in all 3 murders.

07:13.885 --> 07:15.185
His last known victim
was in 2004

07:15.252 --> 07:16.519
and he was never caught.

07:16.587 --> 07:18.988
So he didn't go dormant
by choice. He was locked up.

07:19.056 --> 07:20.190
Well, why not just escape?

07:20.257 --> 07:21.658
If he hadn't sewn
the guard's mouth shut,

07:21.725 --> 07:23.059
we would never know
it was him.

07:23.126 --> 07:24.927
Rossi: He wants us
to know he's back.

07:24.995 --> 07:27.697
We've got his face.
What's his name?

07:27.764 --> 07:30.300
John Doe. He was pulled over
in '04 for a traffic violation.

07:30.367 --> 07:32.767
No registration, no tags.
He carried no I.D.

07:32.835 --> 07:34.670
No way he did 8 years
for that.

07:34.737 --> 07:36.805
They searched the car
and found a gun with a silencer.

07:36.872 --> 07:39.841
A silencer. He was practically
telling them who he was

07:39.909 --> 07:40.942
and no one
made the connection.

07:41.010 --> 07:42.143
It's a federal offense,

07:42.212 --> 07:43.478
carries a 30-year
minimum sentence.

07:43.546 --> 07:44.979
But it was actually
what he did inside

07:45.047 --> 07:46.648
that guaranteed him
life without parole.

07:46.716 --> 07:48.449
He killed two men
while inside.

07:48.517 --> 07:50.117
And never said a word.

07:50.185 --> 07:52.386
Mm-hmm. He spoke
with his fists.

07:52.454 --> 07:55.323
Remaining silent for 8 years
takes a hell of a lot of self-restraint.

07:55.390 --> 07:56.624
Maybe it was
a conditioned response.

07:56.692 --> 07:58.726
Garcia's gathering
all the files from '04.

07:58.793 --> 08:01.128
We'll catch up on the plane.
Wheels up in 30.

08:09.202 --> 08:11.403
Alex.

08:11.471 --> 08:14.043
I'm sorry I didn't
get a chance to see you

08:14.044 --> 08:14.803
before the Seattle case.

08:14.808 --> 08:16.142
Congratulations.

08:16.209 --> 08:21.447
It took a lot of hard work
to get a shot here.

08:21.515 --> 08:22.848
It wasn't easy.

08:22.915 --> 08:27.119
It's been a long time.

08:30.257 --> 08:33.525
I've got a plane
to catch, Erin.

08:34.794 --> 08:36.727
Good luck.

